vestibular information to the vestibular nuclei in the brainstem?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Abducens nerve (cranial nerve VI)","Facial nerve (cranial nerve VII)","Vestibulocochlear nerve (cranial nerve VIII)","Glossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX)","Vagus nerve (cranial nerve X)"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Evestibulocochlear nerve (cranial nerve VIII)\u003C/strong\u003E carries both vestibular and auditory information. The vestibular portion receives input from the semicircular canals and otolith organs in the inner ear, transmitting this information to the vestibular nuclei in the brainstem for processing of balance and spatial orientation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eabducens nerve (cranial nerve VI)\u003C/strong\u003E controls lateral eye movement via the lateral rectus muscle, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Efacial nerve (cranial nerve VII)\u003C/strong\u003E controls facial muscles and carries taste information from the anterior two-thirds of the tongue. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eglossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX)\u003C/strong\u003E provides sensory innervation to the posterior third of the tongue and pharynx, and the \u003Cstrong\u003Evagus nerve (cranial nerve X)\u003C/strong\u003E supplies parasympathetic innervation to thoracic and abdominal organs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The vestibulocochlear nerve (cranial nerve VIII) carries both balance information from the vestibular apparatus and hearing information from the cochlea.","The vestibular portion of cranial nerve VIII synapses in the vestibular nuclei of the brainstem to process balance and spatial orientation."],"references":["Bordoni B, Mankowski NL, Daly DT. Neuroanatomy, Cranial Nerve 8 (Vestibulocochlear) [Updated 2023 May 22]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537359/","Netter, F. H. (2015). Netter\u0027s Cranial Nerve Collection E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98107"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16302"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98107"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-27T15:11:38+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-27T15:12:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8993"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116111"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self":"https://app.emed